    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <add>פרי צדיק עץ חיים ושפ יא תמת תכון לעד</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Fruit of the Righteous is a Tree of Live, and the Lips of Truth
                shall be Remembered Forever.</p>
            <p><hi rend="bold">A Memorial Offering</hi><lb/> Upon the death of that great,<lb/>
                wise, good, and beloved<lb/> man,<lb/> MINISTER AND GUIDE<lb/> OF THE<lb/>
                Congregation “Beth-el-Emeth,”<lb/>
                <placeName>PHILADELPHIA</placeName>.</p>
            <p>ALAS!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName><hi rend="bold">I</hi>saac Leeser</persName> is gathered.
                Woe! He's departed and is no more,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">S</hi>adness and mourning on
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName> fall, for the affliction is sore.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">A</hi>h! thus on the Holy <date>Sabbath</date> his
                spirit ascended on high.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">A</hi>nd faint grew our hearts, and midst weeping
                and wailing, a cry</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">C</hi>ame from Heaven and called him, and broke up
                our circle of joy.</p>
            <p/>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">L</hi>o! where is the scribe, who his wisdom can
                fitly applaud!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ternal his teachings, in all tongues they are
                scattered abroad.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ver abounding in reverence, in wisdom, and
                piety's praise,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">S</hi>till on Holy ground walking he left us exalted
                in grace,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">E</hi>ver in him was our shield, as still on his
                strength we relied,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName><hi rend="bold">R</hi>everend Isaac Leeser</persName>
                enough for our glory; our guide.</p>
            <p/>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Blest</hi> are the righteous. Though dead they still
                live for the truth,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Be</hi> like him, whose loins were girded with
                strength in his youth.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">The</hi> grave we can't know, nor see destruction's
                abyss,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="bold">Righteous</hi> I pray, in God's will, may my end be
                like his.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">ISAAC GOLDSTEIN</persName>, <placeName>137
                    HUDSON STREET, N. Y.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="Note: ">Same <add>?</add> text in Hebrew on the right side of the page; picture
                of <persName>Isaac Leeser</persName> near the top center of the page</p>
        </body>
